<HEAD>

<TITLE>RULE 1167 - Air Stripping Operations</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Nate Natzke">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
(Adopted January 8, 1988)(Rescinded December 2, 1988)
<P>
<B>RULE 1167. AIR STRIPPING OPERATIONS</B>
<P>
Rescinded by the Board on December 2, 1988, in accordance with
the decision of Los Angeles Superior Court case number C677420.(Adopted
January 8, 1988)
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<B>RULE 1167. AIR STRIPPING OPERATIONS</B>
<P>
(a) Definitions
<P>
<OL>
<LI>Air Stripping is a method of treating contaminated water for
the removal of volatile organic contaminants.  The air stripping
process involves the aeration of contaminated water with sufficient
volumes of air that will allow the removal of volatile organic
contaminants by volatilization from water into the passing air.
<P>
<LI>Volatile Organic Compound (VOC) is any volatile compound of
carbon, excluding methane, carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, carbonic
acid, metallic carbides or carbonates, ammonium carbonate, 1,1,1-trichloroethane,
methylene chloride, trifluoromethane (FC-23), trichlorotrifluoroethane
(CFC-11), dichlorodifluoromethane (CFC-12), trichlorofluoromethane
(CFC-113), chlorodifluoromethane (CFC-22), dichlorotetrafluoroethane
(CFC-114), and chloropentafluoroethane (CFC-115).
<P>
</OL>
(b) Applicability
<P>
 The provisions of this rule apply to new and existing air stripping
equipment used for the treatment of water contaminated with volatile
organic compounds.
<P>
(c) Requirements
<P>
After December 1, 1988, a person shall not operate an air stripping
equipment unless an air pollution control device or other process
is used to reduce volatile organic emissions by at least 90 percent
on a mass basis, or to 1.0 pound of VOC or less per day.
<P>
(d) Exemptions
<P>
<OL>
<LI>The provisions of paragraph (c) shall not apply to air stripping
equipment which emit 1.0 pound of VOC or less per day.
<P>
<LI>The provisions of this rule shall not apply to aeration of
wastewater at sewage treatment facilities.
<P>
</OL>
(e) Compliance Schedule
<P>
 The owner or operator of an existing air stripper who elects
to install a control device or modify his operation pursuant to
the requirements of this rule shall submit to the Executive Officer
by June 1, 1988 application for permit to construct and operate
for the system and shall be in full compliance with the requirements
of this rule by December 1, 1988.
<P>
(f) Recordkeeping
<P>
The owner or operator of an air stripping equipment shall monitor
contaminated water and airstream VOC concentrations as required
by the Executive Officer.  Such records shall be retained for
a minimum of two years and shall be made available to the Executive
Officer for review upon request.
<P>
<HR>
<P>

</BODY>
</HTML>
<P>

