<HEAD>
<title>RULE 3007 - Effect of Permit</title>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="SCAQMD">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Nate Natzke 11-21-96">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
(Adopted October 8, 1993)
<P>
<B>RULE 3007. EFFECT OF PERMIT </B>
<P><B>
(a) Effect of Permit</B>
<P>
<ol>
<li>A Title V permit does not convey property rights of any sort,
or any exclusive privilege.
<P>
<li>A written authorization to construct, issued as part of a
Title V facility permit, shall be deemed a permit to construct
for the purposes of all other District Rules and Regulations.
<P>
<li>A written authorization to operate equipment, issued as part
of a Title V facility permit, shall be deemed a permit to operate
for the purposes of all other District Rules and Regulations.
<P>
<li>A Title V facility permit shall have all the rights delineated
in Regulation II for permits including the right of appeal.  
<P>
</ol>
<B>(b) Severability</B>
<P>
 A challenge to any permit condition or requirement raised by
EPA, the facility owner or operator, or any other person, shall
not invalidate or otherwise affect the remaining portions of the
Title V permit.
<p>
<hr>
<p>

</BODY>
</HTML>
