<HEAD>
<TITLE>On-Site Technical Consultation Service </TITLE>
<meta name = "OPERATOR" content = "Lana Bowman">
</HEAD>
<BODY>

 <img src="/icon/newrule1.gif" border=0  align="LEFT" hight=50 width=50><CENTER> <B>SOUTH COAST AIR QUALITY MANAGEMENT DISTRICT'S ON-SITE </B><B>TECHNICAL CONSULTATION SERVICE</B><p><IMG SRC="/icon/line4.gif"></CENTER>

<p>On-site technical consultations are one of the many ways AQMD helps businesses meet today&#146;s air quality standards.  Recognizing that our rules are sometimes difficult to properly interpret and that a business person&#146;s time is limited, AQMD&#146;s Small Business Assistance Office offers an on-site technical consultation service to help business owners:

<UL>
<LI> Identify sources of and ways to prevent air pollution
<LI> Educating and encouraging sound environmental practices
<LI> Providing assistance and liaison with other agency staff on permit processing, application filing, regulatory compliance, and fee issues
<LI> Find sources for financial assistance

</UL>

<P>
All business owners are eligible for this free on-site technical consultation service.
<p>
<P><img src = "/icon/sm_bus00.gif" align = left height =20 width = 50><h3>How to request a free on-site technical consultation</H3>


To request a complimentary on-site consultation, mail your company name and mailing address, (and the name and telephone number of a contact person) along with your request, to:
<CENTER><P>
<STRONG>South Coast Air Quality Management District</STRONG><BR>

<STRONG>Small Business Assistance Office</STRONG><BR>

<STRONG>P. O. Box 4938</STRONG><BR>

<STRONG>Diamond Bar CA  91765-0938</STRONG>
</CENTER><P>
A Small Business Representative will contact your company to make an appointment.  Consultations are scheduled on a first-come, first-served basis with business size and geographic location taken into consideration.
<P>


<P>
If you do not want to mail your request, you may also send your request by <A HREF="mailto:sbao@aqmd.gov">e-mail</A> to: (sbao@aqmd.gov) or call us (800-388-2121).<br><br>
<img src = "/icon/sm_bus01.gif" align = left height =50 width = 20>
<p><br>
<h3>What to expect when help arrives</B></h3>

<P>
Your Small Business Representative will review AQMD rules and regulations which apply to your facility.  During a walk-through of your facility, you and your representative will identify problem areas, evaluate pollution reduction opportunities, and work together to find a permanent, cost-effective solutions.
<P>
Your representative may make recommendations, but cannot provide in-depth engineering design services.  However, your representative can provide you with a list of qualified technical consultants who can help assure proper follow-up on our recommendations.<br><br>
<img src = "/icon/manphone.gif" align = left height = 40 width = 40>
<h3>
Follow-up</h3>
<br>
Be sure to call your representative if you need additional help.  Your small business representative may also check with you from time to time to see if you need further compliance assistance.  Ultimately, you have the responsibility for correcting any non-compliant conditions.
<h3>
Permit Assistance Centers  </h3>
For your assistance, the AQMD also has staff available at the following locations to assist you with your permits or with consultations:
<BR>
<p>
<B>Diamond Bar - AQMD Headquarters</B><br>
Tuesday through Friday, 7 a.m. - 5:30 p.m.
<BR>21865 E. Copley Drive 91765
<BR>(800) 388-2121, FAX (909) 396-3335
<p>
<B>Downey-Energy Resource Center</B><br>
Southern California Gas Company
<BR>9240 E. Firestone Blvd., 90241
<BR>(310) 803-7421
<p>
<B>Los Angeles-Los Angeles City Hall</B><br>
Construction Services Center
<BR>200 N. Spring Street, Room 460, 90012
<BR>(213) 847-4622
<p>
<B>Palm Desert-Coachella Valley Permit Assistance Center</B><br>
73-510 Fred Waring Drive, 92260
<BR>(619) 340-0697
<p>
<B>CAL EPA Permit Assistance Centers</B><br>
(800) GOV-1-STOP
<p>
<B>Baldwin Hills - Crenshaw Plaza</B><br>
Business Revitalization Center
<BR>3650 W. Martin Luther King Jr. Blvd.
<BR>2nd level, #246, 90008
<BR>(213) 290-7100
<p>
<B>Ontario-Inland Empire Permit Assistance Center</B><br>
2151 E. D Street, #203A, 91764
<BR>(909) 391-0723
<p>
<B>Santa Ana-Orange County Permit Assistance Center</B><br>
300 N. Flower St., 1st Floor, 92703
<BR>(714) 834-3379
<p>
<B>Van Nuys-San Fernando Valley Permit Assistance Center</B><br>
14437 Erwin St. Mall, 91401
<BR>(818) 756-7572

<P>To schedule an appointment with a representative at one of these centers, please call (800) 388-2121.
<P>
