<HEAD>
<TITLE>1997 AIR QUALITY MANAGEMENT PLAN</TITLE>

<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="SCAQMD">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Nate Natzke">

</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/icon/logo.gif" HEIGHT=75 WIDTH=56 ALIGN="LEFT">
<P><BR>
<CENTER><B><H2>NOTICE OF PUBLIC WORKSHOP</H2></B></CENTER>
<P>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<P><B>1997 AIR QUALITY MANAGEMENT PLAN
<BR>FOR THE SOUTH COAST AIR QUALITY MANAGEMENT DISTRICT</B></P>

<P>
<TABLE BORDER=1>
<TR>
<TD>
<TD>
<P><B>September 4, 1996 -- 10 a.m.</B>
<BR>Anaheim Marriott
<BR>700 W. Convention Way
<BR>Anaheim, CA</P>
<TD>
<TR>
<TD>
<TD>
<TD>
<TR>
<TD>
<P><B>September 5, 1996 -- 10 a.m.</B>
<BR>Airtel Hotel
<BR>7277 Valjean Ave.
<BR>Van Nuys , CA</P>
<TD>
<P><B>September 5, 1996 - 2 p.m.</B>
<BR>Port of Los Angeles
<BR>425 S. Palos Verdes St.
<BR>San Pedro, CA</P>
<TD>
<P><B>September 9, 1996 -- 10 a.m.</B>
<BR>Palm Desert City Council Chambers
<BR>73-510 Fred Waring Drive
<BR>Palm Desert, CA</P>
<TR>
<TD>
<TD>
<TD>
<TR>
<TD>
<P><B>September 10, 1996 -- 10 a.m.</B>
<BR>Riverside Mission Inn
<BR>3649 Mission Inn Ave.
<BR>Riverside, CA</P>
<TD>
<P><B>September 10, 1996 - 2 p.m.</B>
<BR>Board of Supervisors&#146; Chambers
<BR>385 N. Arrowhead Ave.
<BR>San Bernardino, CA</P>
<TD>
<P><B>September 11, 1996 -- 7 p.m.</B>
<BR>South Coast AQMD Auditorium
<BR>21865 Copley Drive
<BR>Diamond Bar, CA</P>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>
<P>The South Coast Air Quality Management District (District) has scheduled a series of public workshops to discuss the draft proposed <B>1997 revisions to the Air Quality Management Plan (AQMP)</B>.  </P>
<P>The draft 1997 AQMP addresses the PM10 State Implementation Plan (SIP) requirements of the federal Clean Air Act for the South Coast Air Basin.  (PM10 is small particulate matter less than 10 microns in diameter.)  The draft 1997 AQMP is designed to meet both state and federal Clean Air Act requirements for all areas under District jurisdiction, including the South Coast Air Basin, the Los Angeles County portion of the Mojave Air Basin (Antelope Valley), and the Riverside County portion of the Salton Sea Air Basin (including the Coachella Valley).  It addresses all criteria pollutants, including PM10, ozone, carbon monoxide, and nitrogen dioxide.</P>
<P>The draft 1997 AQMP is based upon comments and inputs on the 1994 AQMP, from numerous task forces and working groups (including the PM10 Task Force), AQMP Public Consultation Meetings, and public meetings with the regulated community, various interest groups, and other public agencies.  The draft 1997 AQMP is jointly prepared with the Southern California Association of Governments.  The California Air Resources Board provided input on the statewide consumer products, pesticides, and mobile source control strategy proposed in the draft 1997 AQMP.  </P>
<P>
<B>Issues</B></P>
<P>The draft 1997 AQMP includes new information on key elements such as:</P>
<UL>
<P><LI>current air quality, including special particulate data from the PM10  Technical Enhancement Program (PTEP);</P>
<P><LI>Improved emission inventories, especially for motor vehicles, solvent usage, fugitive dust, and ammonia sources;</P>
<P><LI>A similar, but fine-tuned overall control strategy with continuing emphasis on flexible, alternative approaches, including intercredit trading;</P>
<P><LI>A determination that certain control measures contained in the 1994 AQMP are infeasible, most notably future indirect source measures;</P>
<P><LI>Enhanced modeling for particulates;</P>
<P><LI>Separate analyses for the desert portions within the District&#146;s jurisdiction (the Antelope and Coachella Valleys)</P>
<P><LI>Amendments to the federal Post-1996 Rate-of-Progress Plan and the Federal Attainment Plans for ozone and carbon monoxide;</P>
<P><LI>A Maintenance Plan for nitrogen dioxide; and</P>
<P><LI>An attainment demonstration and State Implementation Plan Revision for PM10.</P>
</UL>
<P>You are invited to participate in the AQMP development process.  Your involvement is essential in building an innovative and technically-sound Plan that draws on the talents of the individual, business, the public sector, and nonprofit organizations.  Please take time to attend one or more of the seven scheduled meetings and share your ideas and comments about how to clean up our polluted air.</P>
<P><B>TO OBTAIN COPIES OF </B><B>DOCUMENTS</B></P>
<P>Copies of the draft 1997 AQMP will be available on or shortly after August 6, 1996 and may be obtained from:</P>
<P>Public Information Center
<BR>SCAQMD
<BR>P O Box 4937
<BR>Diamond Bar, CA 91765-0937
<BR>(909) 396-2039</P>
<P>Copies of the draft 1997 AQMP will also be available at the public workshops.  In addition, copies of the document will be available on the Internet at www.aqmd.gov.</P>
<P><B>SUBMISSION OF DOCUMENTS OR </B><B>COMMENTS</B></P>
<P>The public is requested to send comments, documents or other information relevant to the development of the 1997 AQMP to:</P>
<P>Mr. Melvin Zeldin, Planning Manager
<BR>Planning, Tran., and Info. Management
<BR>SCAQMD
<BR>21865 Copley Drive
<BR>Diamond Bar, CA 91765
<BR>(909) 396-3184</P>
<P><BR>
