<P>
MR. WEDAA MOVED THAT: 1) THE BOARD RECONSIDER ITS ACTION ON RULE
1402; AND 2) MODIFY SUBPARAGRAPH (d)(11) OF RULE 1402 TO ALLOW
METAL FINISHERS TO BE ELIGIBLE FOR A DEFERRAL FROM COMPLIANCE
WITH RULE 1402 BASED ON THEIR COMPLIANCE WITH RULE 1169. THE MOTION
WAS SECONDED BY MR. MIKELS, AND PASSED BY THE FOLLOWING VOTE:
<P>
AYES: Albright, Antonovich, Braude, Burke, Mikels, Paulitz, Wedaa,
Wieder, Wilson, and Younglove.
<P>
NOES: None.
<P>
ABSENT: Lee.
