<HEAD>

<TITLE>PC,LAN,WAN RFP Recommendation</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
   July 14, 1995
<P>
South Coast Air Quality<BR>
     Management District Board
<P>
Recommendation to Qualify Vendors to Provide PC,<BR>
<U>LAN and WAN Replacement Parts and Repair Services</U>
<P>
On May 15, 1995 the District released a Request for Proposals
(RFP) for Personal Computer, Local Area Network and Wide Area
Network Replacement Parts and Repair Services.  The purpose of
the RFP is to pre-qualify vendors capable of providing repair
services and supplies for the District's personal computers and
telecommunication operations.
<P>
In accordance with the District's Consultant Selection Policy
and Procedure, a public notice inviting bids was published in
the Los Angeles Times, L.A. Sentinel, La Opinion, Orange County
Register, Riverside Press Enterprise, AQMD BBS, San Bernardino
Sun, The M/W/DVBE Source, and RFP/Bid Information Line.
<P>
Copies of the RFP were mailed to forty-one bidders (Attachment
A).  Responses were received from two bidders, Microage Computermart
and Mitsuba Corporation.  Staff has completed the evaluation and
selection process and has qualified these two bidders. Both bidders
meet the minimum requirements identified in the RFP.  Staff believes
that these vendors will be able to provide about 80% of parts
and repair services required in support of the District's personal
computer infrastructure.  Items not available from these two vendors
will be acquired in accordance with the District's Administrative
Policies and Procedures.
<P>
THEREFORE, IT IS RECOMMENDED THAT YOUR BOARD
<P>
 --Approve Microage Computermart and Mitsuba Corporation as qualified
<BR>
   vendors who will provide PC, LAN, WAN replacement parts and
repair <BR>
   services.
<P>
  Respectfully,
<P>
  James M. Lents, Ph.D.
<P>
  Executive Officer
<P>
BRW:VCM:RKV:ag
<P>
Attachments
<P>
q:\brdltr\pcrfpltr.doc
