<HEAD>

<TITLE>Library RFP Vendor Recommendation</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
   July 14, 1995
<P>
South Coast Air Quality<BR>
     Management District Board
<P>
Recommendation to Qualify Vendors to <BR>
<U>Provide Library Services and Supplies</U>
<P>
On May 15, 1995 the District released a Request for Proposals
(RFP) for Library Services and Supplies.  The purpose of this
RFP is to pre-qualify vendors to provide various library services
and supplies such as technical and legal books, miscellaneous
book purchases and multi-media materials; subscription services,
including periodical, legal book and miscellaneous subscriptions;
and professional services, including cataloging, inter-library
loan and loose leaf filing.
<P>
In accordance with the District's Consultant Selection Policy
and Procedure, a public notice inviting bids was published in
the Los Angeles Times, L.A. Sentinel, La Opinion, Orange County
Register, Riverside Press Enterprise, AQMD BBS, San Bernardino
Sun, The M/W/DVBE Source, and RFP/Bid Information Line.
<P>
Copies of the RFP were mailed to thirty-nine bidders (Attachment
A).  Responses were received from nine bidders.  Staff has completed
the evaluation and selection process and has qualified all nine
bidders.  All nine bidders meet the minimum requirements identified
in the RFP.  Staff believes that these vendors will be able to
provide about 70% of the required Library services and supplies.
 Items not available from these nine vendors will be acquired
in accordance with the District's Administrative Policies and
Procedures. 
<P>
THEREFORE, IT IS RECOMMENDED THAT YOUR BOARD
<P>
--Approve the list of vendors found in Attachment B to provide
the District <BR>
   Library's services and supplies.
<P>
  Respectfully,
<P>
  James M. Lents, Ph.D.
<P>
  Executive Officer
<P>
