copies of Pages 68 and 69 of the Draft Staff Report on this item,
which had inadvertently been left out, were distributed to Board
members and made available to the public.
<P>
ON MOTION OF MR. PAULITZ, DULY SECONDED, A UNANIMOUS VOTE WAS
CAST OF THE BOARD MEMBERS PRESENT (Absent: Braude and Wilson),
APPROVING AGENDA ITEM NO. 10 AS RECOMMENDED BY STAFF.
<P>
19. Recommendation to Amend the Sole-Source Contract for Measurement
of Ammonia and Volatile Organic Compound Emissions from Livestock
Waste in the South Coast Air Basin
