<HEAD>

<TITLE>Recommendation to Pre-Qualify Vendors to Provide</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Rezvan Ramezani">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
September 8, 1995
<P>
South Coast Air Quality
<P>
Management District Board
<H3><CENTER> Recommendation to Pre-Qualify Vendors to Provide
Various Non-Consultant Services and Supplies <FONT SIZE=5></H3>

<H3></FONT></H3>
<HR>

<P>
On July 14, 1995, the Board approved the release of several Request
for Quotations (RFQs) which would be used to establish a list
of pre-qualified vendors from whom competitive bids may be solicited
for the purchase of various non-consultant services and supplies.
<P>
In accordance with District's Contracting and Purchasing Policy,
a public notice inviting bids was published in the Los Angeles
Times, La Opinion, Orange County Register, Riverside Press Enterprise,
and San Bernardino Sun on June 15 and 22, 1995, and in the M/W/DVBE
Source and the Los Angeles Sentinel on June 14, 1995. In addition
it was also placed on the AQMD's Bulletin Board Services ( BBS)
and RFP/Bid Information Line, and bids were mailed to various
vendors.
<P>
Nine bids were mailed to suppliers of unleaded fuel,and three
vendors (see Attachment) responded with bids by the closing date,
July 28, 1995. All three vendors met the evaluation criteria for
performance, references, experience, and cost factors. These vendors
represent three different refineries and since each refinery's
price per gallon fluctuates per week, staff recommends that all
three vendors be certified as pre-qualified in order that the
best price be obtained each time an order is placed.
<P>
Six bids were mailed to suppliers of photocopy/printing paper
and all six responded with bids by the closing date July 11, 1995.
Two of the bidders (see Attachment) met the paper minimum content
specifications of 35% post-consumer and 15% pre-consumer waste.
The two bids are also cost competitive. Due to the changing conditions
in the recycled paper market and the paper mills' price changes,
staff recommends that the two vendors be certified as pre-qualified
so that the best price can be obtained at the time an order is
placed.
<P>
SCAQMD Board -2- September 8, 1995
<P>
The recommendation was reviewed and approved by the Administrative
Committee at its meeting on August 18, 1995.
<P>
THEREFORE, IT IS RECOMMENDED THAT YOUR BOARD
<P>
--Approve the list of pre-qualified vendors on the Attachment.
<P>
--Authorize staff to establish blanket purchase order agreements
through June 30, 1996.
<P>
Respectfully,
<P>
James M. Lents, Ph.D.
<P>
Executive Officer
<P>
NN:LMJ:lg
<P>
Attachment
<P>
<U>ATTACHMENT</U> 
<P>
<U>Recycled Photocopy/Printing Paper Vendors</U> <U>Unleaded Fuel
Vendors</U> 
<P>
1. Kirk Paper Company 1. POMA Distributing Company
<P>
7500 Amigos Avenue 571 W. Slover Avenue
<P>
Downey, CA 90042 Bloomington, CA 92316
<P>
2. Willamette Industries 2. Pinnacle Petroleum
<P>
